Anthrax, cattle - USA (New Mexico) 980820224525
Anthrax, cattle - USA (New Mexico) (02) 981101203604
Anthrax, cattle - USA (New Mexico) (03) 981115183715
Date: Mon, 16 Nov 1998 13:41:57 +0000
From: DR J PICARD <infek4@op1.up.ac.za>

South African veterinary students are taught to recognise _Bacillus
anthracis_ on blood smears made from herbivors. They are taught to
recognise the organism in smears stained with Romanosky-type stains, as
these are more freely available. The organisms usually are large
brick-shaped purple bacteria with a pink capsule. I agree that aged
Loeffler's methylene blue stain (McFaydean's stain) is better, and would
encourage its use. This stain should still be available in many countries
as it is a counter-stain used in the modified acid-fast stain.
Although newer tests are being developed, these tests should only be used
if they are better (more sensitive and specific) than the "older"
techniques as well as been more cost-effective.
--
Jackie Picard
University of Pretoria,
South Africa
tel: 27-12-5298017
