e-mail: infek4@op1.up.ac.za
[It should be noted that using blood smears works fine as long as the
animal, e.g., dairy cow, has not been on antibiotics when blood smears will
be essentially abacteraemic. Tests based on the presence/absence of
Protective antigen would still work. I think we can now cut this thread. -
